{
  "texts": [
    "User-centric platforms typically use personalized recommendations (Gongane et al., 2024).",
    "Therefore, understandably, social media platforms predominantly utilize personalized (i.e., customized) recommendation systems (Zhang et al., 2024).",
    "This approach leverages a user's actions and engagement on social media platforms as an anchor for analysis (Abdulrashid et al., 2024; Das et al., 2017; Seo et al., 2017).",
    "During the initial stage, conventional recommender systems such as content-based filtering and collaborative filtering were used to deliver suggestions utilizing methods (Shapira et al., 2013; Wang et al., 2013).",
    "Later, however, there has been a significant rise in the number of social media users and the volume of data."
  ]
}